@startuml
' Evaluate chain — ralphctl sprint evaluate (standalone) + nested inside per-task
' Standalone factory: src/application/chains/evaluate/evaluate-flow.ts
' Step trace: load-sprint → load-task → check-already-evaluated → evaluate-task → persist-evaluation
' Note: the per-task chain in execute uses EvaluateAndFixLoopUseCase (multi-round); the standalone chain runs ONE round.
title ralphctl — Evaluate chain (single round, standalone)

autonumber

actor User
participant CLI as "CLI / TUI"
participant SM as "SessionManager"
participant Chain as "Sequential('evaluate')"
participant UC as "Use cases\n(business)"
participant AI as "AI\n(autonomous evaluator)"
database sprint.json
database tasks.json
database evaluations as "<sprintDir>/evaluations/<taskId>.md"

User -> CLI : ralphctl sprint evaluate <taskId>
CLI -> SM : start({ element=createEvaluateFlow, ctx })
SM -> Chain : execute(ctx)
activate Chain

Chain -> UC : LoadSprintUseCase
note right: trace: load-sprint
UC -> sprint.json : findById

Chain -> UC : ShowTaskUseCase
note right: trace: load-task
UC -> tasks.json : findById

Chain -> Chain : task.evaluated === false\n(else short-circuit)
note right: trace: check-already-evaluated

Chain -> UC : EvaluateTaskUseCase
note right: trace: evaluate-task
UC -> AI : spawnHeadless(task-evaluation.md\n+ task + sprint + previousCritique?)
activate AI
note right: model ladder for Claude:\nOpus→Sonnet, Sonnet→Haiku, Haiku→Haiku\nCopilot: same model
AI --> UC : raw output
deactivate AI
UC -> UC : SignalParser.parse → EvaluationSignal\n(dimensions parsed from\n**Name**: PASS|FAIL — finding lines)
UC --> Chain : { outcome, signal, fullCritique }

Chain -> UC : update Task\n(evaluated=true, evaluationStatus,\nevaluationOutput preview ≤2000 chars)
Chain -> evaluations : write full critique\n(harness owns the write,\nnot the AI)
note right: trace: persist-evaluation

Chain --> SM : Result.ok({ ctx, trace })
deactivate Chain
SM --> CLI : completed
CLI --> User : EvaluationSignal\n(passed / failed / malformed)

note over Chain
  Evaluator never blocks — task always
  proceeds. Failed / malformed critiques
  log a warning and persist for later
  review; mark-done still runs.
end note

@enduml
